result.execSummary:
The defendant Dakota D. Hagberg was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery by Prisoners [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.20(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases 15CF345 and 15CF154 called together at 11:27am [mo]
Defendant Dakota D. Hagberg in court, in custody with Attorney Steven J. Luchsinger.   ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA Hall verifies victim rights compliance.

The Court reviews the procedural posture of 15CF345; indicates that a Preliminary Hearing waiver needs to be conducted.
recess: 11:37am--reconvene: 11:42am

As to Case 15CF345:
Mr.Hagberg waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Trial.

Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived
--ADA Hall motions to strike the repeater enhancer in the charging language of the Information
--The Court strikes the Repeater Enhancer by its own hand.

As to Both Cases: 
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; pleas of " Guilty " entered on Case 15CF345 and Count #1 of Case 15CF154; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts pleas, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Joint Motion of the Parties, the Court reads in and dismisses Counts #2 and #3 of Case 15CF154
Sentencing arguments given by Counsel

As to Case 15CF154: 
The Court sentences Mr. Hagberg   to  5  years in the Wisconsin State Prison, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of  2  years, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 3  years.  This sentence is to commence FORTHWITH

The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
 
The Court gives  0   days credit for time already served.

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision:
--Anger Management Counseling
--No Contact with Damien Bakken
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as required by the Agent
--On Case 15CF154 Count #1: to pay costs of $268 plus 250 DNA surcharge= $518.
--to pay Officer Overtime fees in the amount of $118.28

As to Case 15CF345:
The Court sentences Mr. Hagberg to 6 months of confinement; this is to be served consecutive to the sentence in 15CF154; this is to be served in the Wisconsin State Prison System
--Days Credit: 0 days
--The Court orders that the costs and fees of Case 15CF345 be added to the terms of Extended Supervision on Case 15CF154; if the Court is unable to do this then costs and fees of Case 15CF345 is to be converted to civil judgement.
